04/06/2006
MERSIN, Turkey -- At least 15 people were injured in a bombing incident that happened in the southern Turkish town of Mersin on Saturday (3 June), according to local police authorities.
The blast was caused by a device that was activated via a mobile phone and exploded in front of a shop on a crowded street in Mersin's commercial district.
Most injured were pedestrians hurt by falling pieces from windows in the neighbourhood.
No group has thus far claimed responsibility for the blast.
(Zaman, Focus - 04/06/06;
CNN Turk - 03/06/06)
